		)
		(uuid "e485e129-f44a-43e8-a57f-68426224a129")
	)
	(text_box "Micro SD Card (J8A - XUNPU MCS-302S-C1) - removable storage used by the phone for files, firmware updates and user data. U10 (TPD6F003DQDR) is a 6-channel ESD protection array that protects the high-speed SDIO lines (CMD, CLK, DAT0-DAT3) from electrostatic discharge when the user inserts or removes the card. R25 (10k) pulls the tray-detect switch high so the MCU can detect when the shared SIM/SD tray is fully inserted. D-1 improvement: the SD card VDD is now powered from SD_VDD_SW instead of the always-on 3.3V rail. This allows the MCU to keep the SD card unpowered during insertion, preventing accidental voltage coupling between the SD and SIM contacts in the shared tray."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 35.56 7.62 0)
		(size 76.2 21.59)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0.635)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type color)
			(color 0 255 0 0.2)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(face "Arial")
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 1)
				(bold yes)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "e890d1da-3ba1-4ad6-93a3-f7325fd9e3b7")
	)
	(text_box "Motor & Vibration (U12 - DRV2603RUNR) - dedicated vibration motor driver used to provide haptic feedback. The MCU controls the driver using VIB_EN (enable) and VIB_PWM (PWM intensity control), while the DRV2603 supplies the higher current required by the vibration motor M1. C29 (100nF) provides supply decoupling during motor startup. Using a dedicated driver prevents the MCU GPIO from sourcing excessive current and allows programmable vibration strength."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 200.66 251.46 0)
		(size 76.2 15.24)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0.635)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
